comments.body:
in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29607/commits/e7c55d4f4dea4c42b40ff326a17e6884de181ed6:

Is there a reason to prefer `auto` over explicitly mentioning the types? I find it to be more readable as 

```suggestion
    for (const char& c : hrp) assert(c < 'A' || c > 'Z');

    std::string ret;
    ret.reserve(hrp.size() + 1 + values.size() + CHECKSUM_SIZE);
    ret += hrp;
    ret += '1';
    for (const uint8_t& i : values) ret += CHARSET[i];
    for (const uint8_t& i : CreateChecksum(encoding, hrp, values)) ret += CHARSET[i];
```

since in the second and third loop its not actually a character, but an index for the character in the `CHARSET`array. Using `auto c` leaves the impression that its all characters, which is incorrect.

